properties.description: Describes the properties of a Shared Image Gallery.

identity.description: The identity of the gallery, if configured.

location.description: The geo-location where the resource lives

systemData.description: Azure Resource Manager metadata containing createdBy and modifiedBy information.

description.description: The description of this Shared Image Gallery resource. This property is updatable.

provisioningState.description: The provisioning state, which only appears in the response.

sharingProfile.description: Profile for gallery sharing to subscription or tenant

softDeletePolicy.description: Contains information about the soft deletion policy of the gallery.

uniqueName.description: The unique name of the Shared Image Gallery. This name is generated automatically by Azure.

permissions.description: This property allows you to specify the permission of sharing gallery. Possible values are: **Private,** **Groups,** **Community.**

groups.description: A list of sharing profile groups.

communityGalleryInfo.description: Information of community gallery if current gallery is shared to community.

type.description: This property allows you to specify the type of sharing group. Possible values are: **Subscriptions,** **AADTenants.**

ids.description: A list of subscription/tenant ids the gallery is aimed to be shared to.

publisherUri.description: The link to the publisher website. Visible to all users.

publisherContact.description: Community gallery publisher support email. The email address of the publisher. Visible to all users.

eula.description: End-user license agreement for community gallery image.

publicNamePrefix.description: The prefix of the gallery name that will be displayed publicly. Visible to all users.

communityGalleryEnabled.description: Contains info about whether community gallery sharing is enabled.

isSoftDeleteEnabled.description: Enables soft-deletion for resources in this gallery, allowing them to be recovered within retention time.

aggregatedState.description: Aggregated sharing state of current gallery.

summary.description: Summary of all regional sharing status.

state.description: Gallery sharing state in current region

details.description: Details of gallery regional sharing failure.

principalId.description: The principal id of the gallery identity. This property will only be provided for a system assigned identity.

tenantId.description: The AAD tenant id of the gallery identity. This property will only be provided for a system assigned identity.

type.description: The type of identity used for the gallery. The type 'SystemAssigned, UserAssigned' includes both an implicitly created identity and a set of user assigned identities. The type 'None' will remove all identities from the gallery.

userAssignedIdentities.description: The list of user identities associated with the gallery. The user identity dictionary key references will be ARM resource ids in the form: '/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.ManagedIdentity/userAssignedIdentities/{identityName}'.

principalId.description: The principal id of user assigned identity.

clientId.description: The client id of user assigned identity.

createdBy.description: The identity that created the resource.

createdByType.description: The type of identity that created the resource.

lastModifiedBy.description: The identity that last modified the resource.

lastModifiedByType.description: The type of identity that last modified the resource.

lastModifiedAt.description: The timestamp of resource last modification (UTC)

properties.description: Describes the properties of a gallery Application Definition.

location.description: The geo-location where the resource lives

systemData.description: Azure Resource Manager metadata containing createdBy and modifiedBy information.

description.description: The description of this gallery Application Definition resource. This property is updatable.

eula.description: The Eula agreement for the gallery Application Definition.

endOfLifeDate.description: The end of life date of the gallery Application Definition. This property can be used for decommissioning purposes. This property is updatable.

supportedOSType.description: This property allows you to specify the supported type of the OS that application is built for. Possible values are: **Windows,** **Linux.**

customActions.description: A list of custom actions that can be performed with all of the Gallery Application Versions within this Gallery Application.

name.description: The name of the custom action.  Must be unique within the Gallery Application Version.

script.description: The script to run when executing this custom action.

description.description: Description to help the users understand what this custom action does.

parameters.description: The parameters that this custom action uses

name.description: The name of the custom action.  Must be unique within the Gallery Application Version.

required.description: Indicates whether this parameter must be passed when running the custom action.

type.description: Specifies the type of the custom action parameter. Possible values are: String, ConfigurationDataBlob or LogOutputBlob

defaultValue.description: The default value of the parameter.  Only applies to string types

description.description: A description to help users understand what this parameter means

properties.description: Describes the properties of a gallery image version.

location.description: The geo-location where the resource lives

systemData.description: Azure Resource Manager metadata containing createdBy and modifiedBy information.

publishingProfile.description: The publishing profile of a gallery image version.

safetyProfile.description: The safety profile of the Gallery Application Version.

provisioningState.description: The provisioning state, which only appears in the response.

replicationStatus.description: This is the replication status of the gallery image version.

source.description: The source image from which the Image Version is going to be created.

settings.description: Additional settings for the VM app that contains the target package and config file name when it is deployed to target VM or VM scale set.

advancedSettings.description: Optional. Additional settings to pass to the vm-application-manager extension. For advanced use only.

enableHealthCheck.description: Optional. Whether or not this application reports health.

customActions.description: A list of custom actions that can be performed with this Gallery Application Version.

targetRegions.description: The target regions where the Image Version is going to be replicated to. This property is updatable.

replicaCount.description: The number of replicas of the Image Version to be created per region. This property would take effect for a region when regionalReplicaCount is not specified. This property is updatable.

excludeFromLatest.description: If set to true, Virtual Machines deployed from the latest version of the Image Definition won't use this Image Version.

publishedDate.description: The timestamp for when the gallery image version is published.

endOfLifeDate.description: The end of life date of the gallery image version. This property can be used for decommissioning purposes. This property is updatable.

storageAccountType.description: Specifies the storage account type to be used to store the image. Cannot be specified along with storageAccountStrategy. This property is not updatable.

replicationMode.description: Optional parameter which specifies the mode to be used for replication. This property is not updatable.

targetExtendedLocations.description: The target extended locations where the Image Version is going to be replicated to. This property is updatable.

storageAccountStrategy.description: Specifies the strategy to be used when selecting the storage account type. Cannot be specified along with storageAccountType, but can be overridden per region by specifying targetRegions[].storageAccountType. This property is not updatable.

mediaLink.description: Required. The mediaLink of the artifact, must be a readable storage page blob.

defaultConfigurationLink.description: Optional. The defaultConfigurationLink of the artifact, must be a readable storage page blob.

install.description: Required. The path and arguments to install the gallery application. This is limited to 4096 characters.

remove.description: Required. The path and arguments to remove the gallery application. This is limited to 4096 characters.

update.description: Optional. The path and arguments to update the gallery application. If not present, then update operation will invoke remove command on the previous version and install command on the current version of the gallery application. This is limited to 4096 characters.

packageFileName.description: Optional. The name to assign the downloaded package file on the VM. This is limited to 4096 characters. If not specified, the package file will be named the same as the Gallery Application name.

configFileName.description: Optional. The name to assign the downloaded config file on the VM. This is limited to 4096 characters. If not specified, the config file will be named the Gallery Application name appended with "_config".

scriptBehaviorAfterReboot.description: Optional. The action to be taken with regards to install/update/remove of the gallery application in the event of a reboot.

regionalReplicaCount.description: The number of replicas of the Image Version to be created per region. This property is updatable.

storageAccountType.description: Specifies the storage account type to be used to store the image. This property is not updatable.

encryption.description: Optional. Allows users to provide customer managed keys for encrypting the OS and data disks in the gallery artifact.

excludeFromLatest.description: Contains the flag setting to hide an image when users specify version='latest'

additionalReplicaSets.description: List of storage sku with replica count to create direct drive replicas.

osDiskImage.description: Contains encryption settings for an OS disk image.

dataDiskImages.description: A list of encryption specifications for data disk images.

securityProfile.description: This property specifies the security profile of an OS disk image.

diskEncryptionSetId.description: A relative URI containing the resource ID of the disk encryption set.

secureVMDiskEncryptionSetId.description: secure VM disk encryption set id

lun.description: This property specifies the logical unit number of the data disk. This value is used to identify data disks within the Virtual Machine and therefore must be unique for each data disk attached to the Virtual Machine.

diskEncryptionSetId.description: A relative URI containing the resource ID of the disk encryption set.

storageAccountType.description: Specifies the storage account type to be used to create the direct drive replicas

regionalReplicaCount.description: The number of direct drive replicas of the Image Version to be created.This Property is updatable

extendedLocation.description: The name of the extended location.

extendedLocationReplicaCount.description: The number of replicas of the Image Version to be created per extended location. This property is updatable.

storageAccountType.description: Specifies the storage account type to be used to store the image. This property is not updatable.

encryption.description: Optional. Allows users to provide customer managed keys for encrypting the OS and data disks in the gallery artifact.

type.description: It is type of the extended location.

allowDeletionOfReplicatedLocations.description: Indicates whether or not removing this Gallery Image Version from replicated regions is allowed.

aggregatedState.description: This is the aggregated replication status based on all the regional replication status flags.

summary.description: This is a summary of replication status for each region.

region.description: The region to which the gallery image version is being replicated to.

state.description: This is the regional replication state.

details.description: The details of the replication status.

progress.description: It indicates progress of the replication job.

properties.description: Describes the properties of a gallery image definition.

location.description: The geo-location where the resource lives

systemData.description: Azure Resource Manager metadata containing createdBy and modifiedBy information.

description.description: The description of this gallery image definition resource. This property is updatable.

eula.description: The Eula agreement for the gallery image definition.

osType.description: This property allows you to specify the type of the OS that is included in the disk when creating a VM from a managed image. Possible values are: **Windows,** **Linux.**

osState.description: This property allows the user to specify whether the virtual machines created under this image are 'Generalized' or 'Specialized'.

hyperVGeneration.description: The hypervisor generation of the Virtual Machine. Applicable to OS disks only.

endOfLifeDate.description: The end of life date of the gallery image definition. This property can be used for decommissioning purposes. This property is updatable.

identifier.description: This is the gallery image definition identifier.

recommended.description: The properties describe the recommended machine configuration for this Image Definition. These properties are updatable.

purchasePlan.description: Describes the gallery image definition purchase plan. This is used by marketplace images.

provisioningState.description: The provisioning state, which only appears in the response.

features.description: A list of gallery image features.

architecture.description: The architecture of the image. Applicable to OS disks only.

allowUpdateImage.description: Optional. Must be set to true if the gallery image features are being updated.

publisher.description: The name of the gallery image definition publisher.

offer.description: The name of the gallery image definition offer.

sku.description: The name of the gallery image definition SKU.

min.description: The minimum number of the resource.

max.description: The maximum number of the resource.

name.description: The name of the gallery image feature.

value.description: The value of the gallery image feature.

startsAtVersion.description: The minimum gallery image version which supports this feature.

storageProfile.description: This is the storage profile of a Gallery Image Version.

safetyProfile.description: This is the safety profile of the Gallery Image Version.

replicationStatus.description: This is the replication status of the gallery image version.

securityProfile.description: The security profile of a gallery image version

restore.description: Indicates if this is a soft-delete resource restoration request.

validationsProfile.description: This is the validations profile of a Gallery Image Version.

publishedDate.description: The timestamp for when the gallery image version is published.

endOfLifeDate.description: The end of life date of the gallery image version. This property can be used for decommissioning purposes. This property is updatable.

source.description: The source of the gallery artifact version.

osDiskImage.description: This is the OS disk image.

dataDiskImages.description: A list of data disk images.

communityGalleryImageId.description: The resource Id of the source Community Gallery Image.  Only required when using Community Gallery Image as a source.

virtualMachineId.description: The resource Id of the source virtual machine.  Only required when capturing a virtual machine to source this Gallery Image Version.

id.description: The id of the gallery artifact version source.

sizeInGB.description: This property indicates the size of the VHD to be created.

hostCaching.description: The host caching of the disk. Valid values are 'None', 'ReadOnly', and 'ReadWrite'

source.description: The source for the disk image.

uri.description: The uri of the gallery artifact version source. Currently used to specify vhd/blob source.

storageAccountId.description: The Storage Account Id that contains the vhd blob being used as a source for this artifact version.

id.description: The id of the gallery artifact version source.

lun.description: This property specifies the logical unit number of the data disk. This value is used to identify data disks within the Virtual Machine and therefore must be unique for each data disk attached to the Virtual Machine.

sizeInGB.description: This property indicates the size of the VHD to be created.

hostCaching.description: The host caching of the disk. Valid values are 'None', 'ReadOnly', and 'ReadWrite'

source.description: The source for the disk image.

reportedForPolicyViolation.description: Indicates whether this image has been reported as violating Microsoft's policies.

policyViolations.description: A list of Policy Violations that have been reported for this Gallery Image Version.

blockDeletionBeforeEndOfLife.description: Indicates whether or not the deletion is blocked for this Gallery Image Version if its End Of Life has not expired.

allowDeletionOfReplicatedLocations.description: Indicates whether or not removing this Gallery Image Version from replicated regions is allowed.

category.description: Describes the nature of the policy violation.

details.description: Describes specific details about why this policy violation was reported.

uefiSettings.description: Contains UEFI settings for the image version.

signatureTemplateNames.description: The name of the template(s) that contains default UEFI key signatures that will be added to the image.

additionalSignatures.description: Additional UEFI key signatures that will be added to the image in addition to the signature templates

pk.description: The Platform Key of this image version.

kek.description: The Key Encryption Keys of this image version.

db.description: The database of UEFI keys for this image version.

dbx.description: The database of revoked UEFI keys for this image version.

value.description: The value of the key signature.

validationEtag.description: The published time of the image version

platformAttributes.description: This specifies the pub, offer, sku and version of the image version metadata

type.description: This property specifies the type of image version validation.

status.description: This property specifies the status of the validationProfile of the image version.

version.description: This property specifies the valid version of the validation.

executionTime.description: This property specifies the starting timestamp.

name.description: This property specifies the name of the platformAttribute. It is read-only.

value.description: This property specifies the value of the corresponding name property. It is read-only.

targetLocations.description: The target regions where the Resource Profile version is going to be replicated to. This property is updatable.
